The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Islamabad bombing
                                                                                                               Islamabad bombing
                            
	Islamabad, June 6 (Reuters): A suicide bomber killed at least one policeman and wounded three in an attack in Islamabad today, police and city officials said.        
	The bomber targeted an emergency response units offices. He scaled the rear wall and jumped into the compound, but police opened fire on him before he could reach the main building, senior police officer Bin Yameen said.                                                                                                                                                                                     
